  "notes": "CA II is one of the fastest enzymes known — kcat approaches 10^6 s⁻¹. The proton-transfer step (via His64 water wire) is rate-limiting at [CO2] above ~5 mM. Inhibitors that replace the Zn-bound water (sulfonamides) are clinically used as diuretics and for glaucoma."
